Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

In a large #bowl{}, add the tomato chunks with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, toss to coat, then set aside.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Add the @tomato puree{30%grams} and garlic to the pan. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @water{100%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @ciabatta{2}.

Toast the ciabatta halves in your #toaster{} until golden.

Once toasted, drizzle with @oil{}.

Once the sloppy joe mixture has thickened, stir through the @butter{20%grams} until melted.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Remove from the heat.

When everything's nearly ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} to the bowl of tomatoes and toss to coat in the dressing.

Share the toasted ciabatta between your #plates{}.

Top the bases with sloppy joe sauce and sprinkle over the cheese. Sandwich shut with the lids.

Serve your salad alongside and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!